data.title: Adrien Charles Danois (b.1797)
data.meta_description: An etching of Maria Beatrice dEste, Duchess of Massa and wife of Ferdinand of Austria-Este. A full-length portrait turned to the left, wearing jewels in her hair and a lace-trimmed dress with wide panniers and a train. The interior she stands within is decorated with draped fabric, an urn and a small table upon which sits a cushion and crown.
